  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.6.1-stable\r\nCommit hash : 021c3c281629baf2eae967dc2f0a7532ddfdc1fb\r\nOS & Version: macOS 10.12.4 (16E195)\r\nGo Version: go1.8.1\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nAny path should be converted to absolute and should be canonised (resolved if it's symlink).\r\n\r\n`~/geth.ipc` - must work.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n`~/geth.ipc` - __not works__\r\n\r\n`./geth.ipc` - _works_\r\n`$HOME/geth.ipc` - _works_\r\n`${HOME}/geth.ipc` - _works_\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n1. start akasha.app (for example)\r\n1. console `geth attach ipc:~/Library/Ethereum/akasha-alpha/geth.ipc`\r\n1. error: `Fatal: Unable to attach to remote geth: dial unix ~/Library/Ethereum/akasha-alpha/geth.ipc: connect: no such file or directory`\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n_no backtrace_",
